content.detailedDescription:
on friday april 15, 2016 at roughly 830pm, i stepped outside to smoke a cigarette. i usually bring my cellphone along to keep me company, but forgot it inside. i sat on my porch steps looking up at the moon, when a fast moving bright light to the left of the moon caught my attention. it was bright bluish-white and roughly twice the size of a star. it was racing east to west at a very high-rate of speed. 
the sky was cloudless and the moon was a little more than half full. as it flew just beneath the moon, i could see it was disc-shaped. 
within seconds, it was halfway across the sky - and suddenly turned off 'like an old tv set' (it got "staticky" then blipped out).    
 
i waited a couple minutes, hoping it'd re-appear, but no dice.
content.summary: Fast moving, self-illuminated ufo shoots across sky before vanishing

content.detailedDescription:
On the night of thursday, april 14, 2016, at approximately 8:35 pm cst, i went outside onto my back deck to look at the temperature gauge on my new bbq grill (i had just seasoned the grates) and closed up all of the vents on it before going to bed. the evening was clear of clouds and it was a mild 66 degrees (f). i turned and looked up at the night sky and the half-moon that seemed to be resting directly above my position, when i noticed coming from the southwest over top of my roof, along the same position as the moon directly overhead, was a multicolored light (i could distinctly see white, blue, red, yellow, and green sequences) much larger than a star or airplane light. the light appeared to be approximately 500 to 700 feet altitude and completely silent. the light remained lit and moved very slowly toward the moon’s position, so i believed that soon i would be seeing a silhouette of its body as it passed. instead, it moved just to the north of the moon’s position in the sky, and began to slow down, at times remaining completely still and at other times slowly moving along its course. then, as it moved along a steady pace, it began to blink out, turning on and off completely, as i was unable to fully see its presence at times. i pulled out my flashlight (i used a flashlight to see my temperature gauge so as not to draw bugs to my back deck light) and began flashing it on and off in the direction of the light—and it began to flash back at me! at times it flashed its light (soft light, but definitely multiple colored wavelengths) so brightly that it appeared as big as the bobbed head of a sewing-pin and perfectly round in shape—and much larger and brighter than venus or jupiter. it began to move slowly around until it had changed direction from 104º moving east to 124º southeast. 
afraid to lose sight of the light, i called for my boys to come witness what i was seeing (my wife was in bed asleep and i did not tell them what they were about to see). my youngest was in the shower, but my oldest son (15) came outside onto the deck and i demonstrated what direction i wanted him to look in. instantly he noticed the light and how it appeared to be flashing us back every time i flashed it with my flashlight. he, too, noticed that it was the color of the “rainbow” and that it was “bright and big.” then while we were watching the first blinking light, another light at equal altitude as the first came up from behind the first object, traveling 346º north at a speed somewhat faster and smoother than a small cessna plane. only this second object was completely white (soft white light, almost a vanilla color), silent, and as large as the first object (about the size of a sewing-pin head). it remained lit the entire time that we observed it (about a minute and a half) and had no other lights (flashing or otherwise) on it. while the second seemed to disappear to the north over some trees, we continued to observe the first flashing light and continued to flash my flashlight at its direction; insofar as it, too, continued to flash its light back at us the entire time, sometimes remaining off for a minute, only to burst with intensity as it flashed back at us. at times the light scintillated slowly and at other times very quickly. it, too, then began to continue on its course until it became difficult to see because of trees, due mostly to its distance from our position at that point (about a mile or so). the entire duration of time watching the flashing light (along with the interruption of the white light) lasted from 8:35 pm to 8:55 pm—a total of 20 minutes! 
my second son (13) came to the back deck, and we all waited to see if anything else was going to take place. we waited for about 20 minutes, when suddenly the second lighted object returned from the north at 9:20 pm, traveling 116º southeast at approximately the same rate of speed as before. it remained an intense soft white color and had no flashing characteristics whatsoever. maintaining its speed, the light appeared to slowly change course directly over our position, traveling 90º east, where after about 4 seconds it instantly disappeared or “cloaked” as my oldest stated. i had witnessed the same soft white lighted object—same size, color, speed, and altitude—on april 7, 2016, at about 8:45 pm cst. and like this evening [april 14], it was traveling due north, but when two small-bodied airplanes approached its position from the southwest, it made an abrupt 90 degree angled turn east toward the capitol, only to disappear entirely after a few seconds. both of these lights, the flashing multicolored light in particular, gave the impression to me and my oldest son to have intelligence. my youngest, too, believed that the entire second event seemed “strange.”
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Two objects, one white and the other multicolored, interacting with observers

content.detailedDescription:
About 9:58pm eastern time my wife and i were looking out the sliding door window to the east.   she saw an orange light that wasn't blinking and was heading westward at a steady speed like most night time air traffic.  we opened the door to look and as it got closer we realized there was no sound.  then as it got almost a straight line to the south it started disappearing in a clear sky.
a minute later we saw another one and it was the same exact thing.  a minute after that we saw the third one which appeared to be heading a little more southwest and as it got closer it winked out also.  no blinking lights, no sound and some pretty good stealth.
content.summary: 3 different orange lights in 3 minutes coming from the east heading west- southwest

content.detailedDescription: In my front yard. i immediately thought the items were out of place. yelled to my husband to come out. appeared as fire balls. thought it was fire debris. seemed to be descending one passed the other and then they appeared to move fast and steady until out of site. they just faded in the horizon clouds. it was significant enough for me to report. i haven't  seen anything like it.
content.summary: Fire like objects lower then a plane..One passed the other

content.detailedDescription:
It was a over cast and cloudy day, with a chance of showers. my four kids just got home from school and they were riding their bicycles, as i was watching them and doing yard work, around 16:00 hrs. 
i stopped yard work, facing north, to watch the kids and one of my daughter's, (age 7) rode her bike up to me, stopped and asked me; "what's that?".... i looked westward and saw a black dot, just below the clouds heading eastward and told her; " it's a helicopter.... 
as i started to go back to doing yard work. my daughter, still looking the this object, yelled out; "it's a flying car!".... me, looking down the neighborhood street, asked her; " where?".... lol. and she pointed west and said; "no!.. up there!" 
as i looked and saw this object get closer; i could see that it wasn't a helicopter!.... the object looked black in color, with wear..(like it did a lot of traveling) and rectangular, in shape, with rounded edges. there was a light, white in color, at each corner of the triangle, with what looked like a thruster in the center? it was traveling in a straight line, as it was slowly rotating and didn't made a sound.
i told my daughter to keep her eyes on it, so that i could get my binoculars out of my truck; in which we both and the truck, were on our driveway. 
as i looked through the binoculars. i could see that it had no numbers or letters on it and this was not a helicopter nor a plane; (being, that we do live nere a very small airport, with cesena's flying in and out all the time.. but, it wasn't a good day to fly.... due to the weather. and this object wasn't a drone either; for the fact that it didn't have any propellers and it was flying too high.)
it flew eastward and suddenly changed direction and went back the other way! it flew then, westward, slowly rotating and then stopped, mid point to were we first saw it. by then; i could see that it had a dome on top, as it had a smaller white light on top of it, too.
it hovered for a few seconds, while still rotating slowly and then, it started spinning faster; just below the cloud line, still...
as i looked at it. it started to look more like a saucer, as it was spinning. and then, there was like a flash... and the object shot straight up into the clouds!.... felt like i was in a dream, while looking at this object.. (from the distance and the height of this object. i would say that it had to be approximately 8 ft. high and 40 to 50 ft. wide? and maybe, even the size of a 2 or 3 bedroom home...?) my daughter and i saw this object for approximately 2 minutes...?
i made a model of it, out of styrofoa, because i got a very good look at this object, through my binoculars....
(not sure how to post the pictures of my model, that i made, on the files part....?
sorry......
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Triangular with rounded edges, thruster at center with light at each corner, dome on top.

content.detailedDescription: My boss happened to open his front door ,checking weather,looked up and saw a light moving along the sky. he noticed two other lights coming from separate directions, these formed a straight line with an equal gap between each. then they stayed stationary for approximately 30-40 seconds, then started to move forwards. they travelled along moving upwards until out of eye sight.No sound was heard. he managed to photograph these several times , which a are attached.
content.summary: Three lights that started off from separate directions formed a line and moved away

content.detailedDescription:
I was on the roof of the building i work at trying to figure out a problem with air conditioning unit. i went to sit down on a ledge, i glanced upwards to the smoggy mountains and then all of sudden i see a big black somewhat triangle shaped object moving super fast.  this object made no sound .   it was flying about legal limit a airplane can fly at over a city.   

this is second time in the last two nights i've seen this type of object. at the same time too 8:30pm.  same rooftop.    


when it flew over i instantly tried to run towards it and try to get my ipod out to video it but as fast as i could move it was gone.   

as i looked at it there was a pair of wings(not airplane type wings) they looked like very thin straight  like an old metal windmill but as i said very thin with little lights on the very end of the wings.


the wings folden in very quick into the craft and expanded out just as fast. it then vanished into thin air didn't even reach the smog.  



my heart was beating fast and i was eager to see it again as this is second time i've seen this type of craft in two nights. 

best way to contact me is my cell 714 833 9838 i'm on study until noon every day anytime past that i can be reached directly
content.summary: Semi triangle, black- brown color pattern had some type of wings expanded and closed in

content.detailedDescription: I stepped out on the front deck of my house to have a smoke, i casually looked up and saw a bright star like orb moving quite swiftly and smoothly, faster than a plane, no sound, looked like a large star i could see it so clear. it moved from a n/w to s/e direction. i watched it for about 4 min. then it slowly dimmed then went out like turning off a light switch. i'm out every night starring at the sky, i see planes of all kinds i'm very familiar with known aircraft my father is a former pilot, this was not a plane or helicopter. i know what i saw and it was not from this planet, unless there is technology we don't know about.
content.summary: White star like orb moving across the sky within our atmosphere, about a mile high.

content.detailedDescription: I had been taking a series of photo's from tobermory to lions head ontario, of an unusual looking cloud or plane trail formation.  i took pictures on and off for the hours drive there.  when we arrived at moore st., my husband and i went into the building together.  during the time spent there, i was feeling ill, so i excused myself and went back to sit in the truck.  before i went in the truck, i looked up at the remaining unusual cloud formation and thought why not take another picture.  i took the picture, looked at it, noticed the sphere in the picture and proceeded to take a second picture, and the sphere, was not present, in it.  i don't know if this is a camera thing or a real orb.  i would like to know as i keep my eyes to the skies all the time, but have yet to see anything until today in a photo only, not in person.  i am submitting all the photo's i took of the cloud formation to show you why i thought it was unusual, the photo of the sphere in the tree is the second last one i believe in the sequence taken. i have 35 pictures in total following the cloud/plane exhaust formation?  taken over an hours approx. length of time.
content.summary: It was only seen in the photo, i seen nothing before or after taking the picture

content.detailedDescription:
-date: april 14, 2016
-time: estimated around 2025-2030 at first contact
-location:  north carolina i-40 east (estimated to be.                    between exit 355 and 364)

•saw two flying objects in sky
- [object 1] appeared to be a helicopter because of the lack of illumination from lights
- [object 2] was close behing it and had brighter lights and a noticeable blinking light like a normal plane.

•as i got closer i noticed object 1 didn't have a blinking light like most aircrafts do and had a red light on top where i thought was the tail of the helicopter.

•object 2 was still identifiable as a fixed wing aircraft

•i got closer underneath the two objects and noticed object 2 silhouette matched what i first anticipated it would be, a fixed wing aircraft. it's lights were located at the nose and both wing tips and we're very bright. presumed to be military as their aren't any commercial airports nearby for it to be so low to the ground. 

•object 2 was unidentifiable. it wasn't what i thought it was, that being a helicopter. it wasn't even identifiable as a privately owned aircraft like a propeller plane. the silhouette appeared to be triangular. from underneath, it had a bright light at its frontal point and two dimmer lights at the remaining rear points. all three lights much dimmer compared to object 2. the front light seemed to reflect the underside of the aircraft which emphasized its triangular shape. the red light was no longer visible, possibly being located on the top of the aircraft. 

•the objects were about as close as a closed fist held at arms length.

•object 1 appeared as large as my finger tip if my arm was extended before me. object 2 was of similar size which surprised me as it appeared small due to dimness of lights.

•lost sight of the aircrafts as they passed to the left-rear side of my vehicle. last seen moving in a northeastern direction.

i was first intrigued by the event because i don't usually see aircraft in the night sky in this area. especially so low to the ground where i could see silhouettes. and what also intrigues me was the proximity of them. at first glance one was definitely escorting the other but i realized one was following the other ( object 2 following object 1). after that realization and with everything detailed above in addition to the fact that ft bragg army base (which has an airfield)  was relatively close, i figured that this was a ufo being tailed by a military aircraft or it could be just a new aircraft. maybe i'm just crazy.
content.summary: Triangle with dim white lights and possibly a red light on top

content.altitude: Treetop, 500 Feet or Less, Over 500 Feet (under cloudcover)
content.detailedDescription: It was about 9-9:30 when mi friend and i was outside chilling having our conversations when all of a sodden mi friend stopped talking and told me to look at the sky, that he is seeing oval shape figure with bright green and white flashing lights just waiting there in the sky and as soon as i turned the hovering shaped figure just waiting there made a 360 and all of a sudden it all disappeared and left a small trail of a bright green beam left behind and suddenly disappearing.
content.summary: Its was oval shape with green and white flashing bright lights.

content.detailedDescription:
1. was walking my dogs at the park on 84th and milky way st on thornton colorado.
2. then i usually look up the sky to see airplanes when i spotted this slow moving object that look square, no lights visible. i ran inside the house to grab binoculars.
3.I thought it was an airplane flying slow
4. the object move like a blanket on the sky with no binoculars, when i put the binoculars it was an orange snake type object moving with what appeared to be an invisible coat.
5.I wanted to see it , but when i zoom in with binoculars i felt scared.
6.The object move north and increase altitude.

there were no light visible until i zoom with binoculars.
content.summary: Invisible cloak square object with an orange light moving like an 8

content.detailedDescription:
my wife and i were driving when she asked, what's that. when i glanced over i caught a glimpse of a light hovering but it disappeared to fast to tell. 20 seconds later, we turned the corner and from a different direction then before, this bright ball came so fast at us, we had to duck in the car cause we thought it was gonna hit the car. it had more then our attention. we lived on the street we just turned to, so right away i got my camera on my cell phone. then it happened. 2-3 more came flying at us. i didn't aim the camera, i just hit the button to snap pictures.. in a few minutes, it was all over. 
   what we thought was a glowing ball, was that. you can see it in the pictures i caught. the fascinating thing we found though was rays around the ball (like the planet saturn). we couldn't see these rings with the naked eye. it shows in the pictures also they touch the pavement, so it did get fairly close to the ground..It flew so fast towards the ground, i still don't know how it could possibly not of crashed. i mean this thing was flying at a speed you couldn't imagine, and instantly stop! the one stopped and flew back from almost the direction it came. and it took off as fast as it came. 
   the other interesting photo was the windows photo. there isn't a house on our street that looks like it. we also didn't see this, as all we seen was a glowing ball. its an odd photo with one window area (perhaps a door), not lit up at all. figures appear to be staring out or something. its kind of a spooky picture, cause i really don't know what i'm looking at.. where's the glowing ball cause that's all i see.I still have the original cell that took these pictures too.
   since this encounter, we had one more, but that's another ufo encounter. eyes to the sky.
content.summary: Glowing ball that hovered, took off hyper speed, came back different directions, flew back from directions it came..So so fast

content.detailedDescription:
About this day i was fishing in a small river in the country side in holland , it was in the afternoon on a nice sunny day. i don't know why i looked up and then saw this about 10 - 12 ft  round very shiny bright orange florescent ball, it was hovering about 3 ft above the ground and only about 50 ft away from me, it made no noise, it had no windows or doors or wings or legs etc-- it was just hanging there, i then thought that it maybe a balloon or so, so i then walked towards it to see it up closer but then it start to move towards my left and kept the same distance, so then i started to run to it and it kept the same distance, then a barbed wire came up but it went up and over and came down to the same about 3 ft above the ground as i kept to follow it there came a row of pine trees like 50 ft or more high so i think that it maybe will get stuck there, by that time it was about 150 ft in front of me and it stopped still for a sew seconds but then it moved about 10 th degree from vertical to the wright and in a second it was gone in the clear sky.
i knew then that it was not a balloon but a ufo, i am sure that it was checking me out or so, i somehow never told any one for 30 years as i think that they would not believe me and then i only told my wife and sister. so in all this time i seen this thing (it) for no less then 6 to 10 minutes. i never forgot it for more than 55 years.
casey
content.summary: 10 ft diam, bright fluresent orange ball like ufo , checking me out ??

content.detailedDescription: It is tamilnadu and i live in tirupur city .On a usual night i was just enjoying the stars as it was bright.It was like 9.30pm.Suddenly i felt like i m covered by a tent a large shadow appeared around me from no where around me when i saw straight up i could see a disk shaped space craft that had a light that snapped like a crop circle i ve seen before in google.It was illuminating and the surface wwas black and grey.It had a diameter of like 150ft it was huge and sounded a hmmm sound which was powerful.I saw it for about 1min and suddenly it ascended up by which the surface starting rotating in a great speed and in a wink the object was no more to be seen.
content.summary: It hovered above my head straight above i saw the shadow around me. it stood as if watching me and suddenly hovered up very fast

content.detailedDescription: Was around 10 pm at my house when i went on my back deck and noticed what i thought at the time was a star to the south west in the distance right above the tree line. it caught my attention because it was pretty bright for a star and it was flickering pretty rapidly between white, blue, red, and green. i figured it was just a star or planet. about a half hour i went back out and saw it was in the same spot decided to see if i could find out what it was with my sky view app that shows everything in the sky but no planets were there and went back inside. i had my dad come out and look at it but he didn't think anything of it. later i went back out after 11 pm and it was gone. i didn't know what to think and went back in and after 20 minutes i decided put on my shoes and decided to walk to the my back yard on top of a hill. i was looking where were it was before for a couple of minutes and then suddenly it reappeared in the same spot like it was. it then turned to a white light and started moving west and the light transformed into a red blinking light, then a clear flashing light. it then changed direction and went north turning back into a white ball of light. while traveling north along the hill line it stopped for a moment, then continued to travel north until it was out of sight. i lost sight of it around 11:45 pm. i would say it was only a couple of miles away from me at first until it started moving. i live right by a small airport so i've seen a lot of planes in this area and this was no plane. i contacted a friend who lives about ten miles away to see if he noticed anything in the sky also and he said he saw the same thing moving around 9:45 pm while driving home.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Was star like orb that was flashing, changing lights and colors. it disappeared and then reappeared then traveled. the encounter was over an hour.

content.detailedDescription: I pulled into the local dog park so i could stop and take pictures of the many chemtrails that were being laid out that morning of april 1, 2016, including one that had spread out to cover the sun. using my smart phone, i was taking a panoramic photo to fit them all in. when i got home and looked at the photos and saw an orb shaped object close to the sun. i did not notice it at the time i was taking the photo as i was in a hurry and the sun was in my eyes. i later used my touch screen to zoom in on it and saw the interesting surface pattern. not sure if it is light play or something else. i used brightness settings and color adjustment on my zoomed in copy to see if i could see any details. since i did not see it at the time the photo was taken, i do not know how it behaved.
content.summary: Captured on digital photo accidentally while taking photos of chemtrails across the sun.

content.detailedDescription:
The date of the incident is approximate due to it happening when i was a child. i was around 9 or 10 years old if i had to guess.

my brother, father and i were visiting my grandmother at her home one evening.  it was already dark outside and we were preparing to leave to go home.  i was inside watching tv with my brother and my father was outside talking to my grandmother.

dad stuck his head inside and told me to come out and look at something.  when we ran outside, my father and grandmother were staring up at something.  following their gazes i looked south from her back yard and just above the treeline i saw a large triangle shaped object with a singular light on each corner and one bright light in the center. it was very typical of the triangle craft that are so often reported. the craft moved from east to west at a very slow speed and low altitude.  it made no sound that i can recall.  

as we watched the craft for several minutes my grandmother asked my father what it was and we all had a conversation about whether it was an airplane or not.  it was clear to everyone that it was not an airplane.  the craft went out of sight to the west.

witnesses to the event were my brother, father and my grandmother (deceased). there is a civilian airport approximately 10 miles south of the location. as someone who was already an avid aviation enthusiast and currently a military aviator, i can honestly say that i do not know what i saw that evening.
content.summary: Older incident: triangle shaped craft observed low level above trees

content.detailedDescription:
I was on my bicycle headed towards walmart. i stopped at the bridge to take pictures of the awesome sky. the parking lot behind grease monkey's was perfect for sky observing because it didn't many buildings or trees obstructing the sky.

i whipped out my cellphone, and took a snapshot of the sky. after the second picture, i went back and looked at the pictures more closely to make sure they came out just right, and noticed a white star like object in front of the clouds. i looked up and could not see the object. so i took another picture of the same area. the white object appeared in the third photograph, slightly to upper right of its previous location. it was moving. again, i looked up, and wasn't able to see the object. since i couldn't see the object, and it only appeared on photograph, i just took random pictures of that area, trying to track the movement.

after 6 random pictures, the object must have disappeared to the south east high above the horizon. my educated guess is it noticed i was taking pictures, and moved into the clouds to conceal itself.

i left that parking lot and continued on to walmart.

after returning from walmart, i plugged my cellphone to the computer, and viewed those pictures i had taken earlier. i noticed the white object in 6 of the 10 pictures that were taken.

***

my cellphone is a nokia lumia 920, and normally takes excellent night pictures as a smartphone. sorry for the fuzziness as i was too excited to adjust my exposure values, and the camera probably had fingerprints all over it.
content.summary: Ufo caught on camera. wasn't visible without camera

content.detailedDescription: At 9:20 pm i went outside to smoke a cigarette, a bright light caught my eye to west over my neighbors house, not sure if it was a flash that caught my attention or just the size and brightness of the object.  my fiancé and i watched as a large round very bright object traveled across the sky.  at first i thought it was a plane but it had no flashing lights and made no sound.  we watched for a few minutes than a low flying plane that had just taken off from the airport went past between us and the object. the object hovered for a moment, the plane past and we watched the object just vanished.  there were no clouds in the sky.  this is not the first time i have seen such an object with this shape and brightness, but it is larger than the others in the past.  those ones were small like a basketball and at ground level zigzagging between trees.  this is the first time seeing one so big.  i wish i would of had my phone or camera on me.
content.summary: Watched bright light travel fast than hoovered as low flying plan past and it vanished

content.detailedDescription: Out gazing and letting the dog. clear warm evening. watching the air traffic. noticed a star about the size of sirius with a similar magnitude brightness slowly moving above me. aligned a power pole to make sure it was in fact moving across the sky, it was....Watched it for a few minutes debating on grabbing my phone to record it. just as i was going to grab my phone it disintegrated within a second to a very small red ball and completely disappeared.
content.summary: Starlite object moving north ne, faded to red dot and disappeared

content.summary: Driving home saw a blue light that changed into something that looked like a donut  disc.

content.detailedDescription:
Wednsday night at about 9:27p i took my dog for his walk near my house.
i was scanning the sky for anything unusual. the sky was clear and the moon was out. i was on still creek drive getting ready to cross the street when i thought i saw a star move from the corner of my eye to my left as i was going west. i went across the street and now could see it was moving, it was starlike white constant light that was about 10 o'clock high from the south west heading in a straight line to north east and quickly became smaller and fainter until it was not visible. my feelings were i thought it was a star but then it moved soo quick and vanished, i was in awe at how it moved.  it reminded me of the spheres i had seen before only i could not see what its surface was like..All i saw was light.
content.summary: Between 9:27p to 9:29p while walking dog saw medium bright star move

content.detailedDescription:
It was around mid may-ish, 2004.  i walked out the back door to have a smoke.  it was about 12:20am.  sky was dark (little to no mooon at all).

i always look up at the sky at night and this night was no different.  clear skies...Great for cosmic viewing!  as i was looking up, i noticed something out of the corner of my right eye.  it seemed like the stars were vanishing.  i turned and looked in that direction (n/nnw) and i could clearly see a very large triangular (delta) shaped "craft" of some sorts, moving across the sky in a s/sse direction, directly overhead.

this craft had no lights and emmited no sound either, but, i could hear it moving through the air above me.  this craft was very large....300' - 500' approximate guestimation.  as far as i could tell, it had to have been between 500' - 1000' above ground, but as it was the middle of the night, it was hard to judge that accurately.  but it was close enough that i heard it "move" through the air overhead.  it was moving at a good clip too.

i froze in disbelief and just followed it as it moved silently across the sky, covering up and then uncovering stars as it moved.  hairs stood up on my body.  came to the crashing conclusion that i had witnessed an unidentified flying object sail over my head.

i kept it quiet for almost two years until a friend of mine told me his story of seeing the exact same craft i had seen.  everything was identical.  

it has taken me 10 years since i spoke to that friend about it, to work up the courage to report this to your group.

i'm most definately not crazy, lol....And have always been of sound mind and body.  i know what i saw, and there's nothing that could explain what i saw.

anyways, that's about all i can tell you.  haven't experienced anything similar since...But i'm always watching!

cheers!

michael collins
content.summary: Orangeville, ontario, canada ufo moving overhead in the night sky.

content.detailedDescription:
I was walking my dog around the block like i do almost ten times a day, on a very overcast day. i heard what i thought was a regular passenger jet, and i looked up expecting to see a normal 737 looking plane. instead, i saw what appeared to be much longer than a 737 and it had two very distinct pairs of parallel wings, in addition to the small blur of the tail wings i could make out. the plane wasn't going particularly fast, and it was low like it might be coming in for a landing several miles away. 

i tried to make sense of what i saw before taking my phone out, and bringing up the camera. i thought it could possibly be a plane carrying a glider, but it looked all one piece - both in person and in the picture/video. i also considered that it might be a drone, but like i said, i looked up because i heard what i thought were the engines of an airliner not the buzzing of a drone. i believe this object is definitely man-made, but i think it's either an experimental aircraft or some new kind of cloud seeder. i tried to look up pictures of anything similar, both in drones and planes, but couldn't find anything.

i also think that it was flown on an overcast day on purpose, to try and conceal it better. i haven't seen anything like this on a clear or cloudy day before, or at all for that matter. the picture i got shows the wings better than video, but the video (while it looks like a cylinder) shows it's longer than a normal aircraft. i tried to zoomout a little to add height perspective, but it's still a pretty bad vid.

does anyone know what this was?
content.summary: Looked like a very long plane with 2 sets of wings in addition to the ones on the tail.
